caption: I went to this place because the other Ethiopian restaurant i used to go to wasn’t that great anymore. (Blue Nile restaurant) I was so satisfied with my experience at Asmara. -The food was so flavorful!!! -Everything on the menu was available. -Amazing options for both Vegan and meat dishes. -The server was incredibly sweet. Definitely one of the best spots for Eri/Ethio food.

What can I say about such pleasant and clean place? The staff is friendly, the food is very tasty - mind blowing! Good portions, fair price. Comfort food.  I’m in love with this place and the way the restaurant is maintained!
My favorite restaurant in Boston

Easily one of my favourite restaurants in the Boston area. Amazing food, great portions for a good price, and even if you stuff yourself full of food, you don't get the stone-stomach because the food is light. Their mixed platter is amazing; pair that with some honey wine and some Eritrean coffee, and your evening is a happy one. Waitress is always very welcoming and friendly and always good for a laugh. Great place; if you don't go, you're a fool.

One of my favorite restaurants in Boston.  The food is so down to earth and delicious, and the staff is extremely kind and caring of the work they do.  Highly recommend the Begeeh Mloukhiya but I've loved all the dishes I've tried here.
Such a great spot for delicious authentic Eritrean cuisine. Go there often and the food and service never disappoint. Highly recommend this restaurant.
I love this place!!

Wow! A great Eritrean food - Very tasty, some spicy and I would recommend to go on the "Sega Bebaynatu" combination, Meat or Veg, both are amazing. A very nice hospitality with African music in the background.

Wonderful food with lots of flavor.  The veggie and meat combo plates are a good option for sampling lots of everything, although neither comes with the jumbo shrimp (which I recommend as well!).  Dining is family-style, so it's a great place to go with close friends and family.  For take-out, packaging can be a little messy, but personally don't mind the different sauces running together... just be aware if you're on a bike that you need to be able to keep the packaging horizontal.  Decor is low-key.  I've only ever seen one waitress, but she's surprisingly efficient and calm even when there are lots of customers.

I loved the food. It was flavorful and very african in culture. I love the scenery of objects, and art of Africa. And the selection of foods and drinks. It's very natural with fantastic bread you use as spoons for the meal, everything is fresh and I enjoy the seating/tables. 10/10 would recommend.
Love the place! Ordered the appwtizer.Salasita.vegetarian and non vegetarian  😋 plates were amazing

The Food is absolutely amazing, my friends and I come here anytime we want wonderful flavorful food. The only complaint I have is that the portion sizes are small, but they seem too large for my friends so maybe I just eat a lot.
Delicious, best food
Delicious every time!
Favorite food in the city. Their takeout during the pandemic has been a staple. Awesome people working there and amazing food!

Amazing; food is just as good as always. If you have not been; check it out. Even though they don't offer reservations, you'll have no trouble finding a table. Absolute treat, and they also offer take out.

Food was delicious. Generous portions, great pricing, outstanding service, and fast preparation. We got the combination meat platter which. Definitely recommend if you haven't been here before. Will definitely be coming back.

We love Asmara. The food is always delicious, the portions are generous, and the wine is great. But there are lots of places you can go for good food and generous portions in Central Square (even during the pandemic). Asmara stands out because of the sense of community that Saba and the team have created. You're not a faceless cypher when you walk in the door, you're family. I'd rather pop my head in, say hello, and take a deep whiff of the spices coming out of the kitchen than sit down for a full meal at most restaurants on the block. Thanks, Asmara!
This restaurant is first-rate and spacious, the menu was delicious and the prices were very economical. quickly, efficient service and very attentive waiters. Recommended.
Ordered here for takeout today, and this place was really amazing. Food was ready within 15 minutes, and tasted amazing. Highly recommend

Sooo good! We got Sega Bebaynetu and Ahimilti Bebaynetu for takeout (during COVID19 stay at home) to have a taste of everything. The flavors and spices were perfectly balanced. One of those meals where even when you’re getting too full you can’t stop taking another bite. Portions were generous and plenty of injera came with both. Can’t wait to dine-in when it’s safe to!
Amazing restaurant! Great service, great food would recommend.
Great Eritrean restaurant
Very flavorful dishes, outstanding service
The food is not good.
Very tasty!

I love love love Ethiopian food. My roomate in college was ethiopian and used to love cooking so I have been spoilt. I used to go to Asmara often but hadn't been in a year and oh dear it has gone down. The food was attrocious - the tomatoes in the salad were actually spoilt and my stomach is already hurting. The dish we ordered was not tasty either. It is very disappointing as this was my favorite Ethiopian place in Boston/Cambridge but unfortunately that's the last time I'm going. It's not worth the emergency room visit or puking my guts out.
Delicious food & Friendly staff! A gem you don’t want to miss when you’re in Cambridge. We had two combo pates, one vegetarian the other meat, and four people couldn’t eat all of it.
Best place for Eritrean / Ethiopian food around. I'll travel an hour or more for this place.
Good Ethiopian food, multiple seating/eating options available. The menu is good, but could use more choices.
Great food and flavors. I love the special with saute eggplant, okra& tomatoes, spinach, and pumpkin with meat sauce. Just delicious!

One of the worst Ethiopian/Eritrean places you can go to. We ordered 6 plates but the sizes were so small and also the taste was not good. Ordered mango juice as a drink and it was all thin mango flavored water. Would give them 0 starts if possible. Worst customer service I have ever had in a habesha restaurant!

Authentic Ethiopian restaurant. Try a new way to consume your food. Best if in group of 3 or 4. Ask for recommendations based on spice tolerance. Excellent service and atmosphere. Not crowded or suffocating. Not expensive either.

Horrible customer service! The main waitress at the restaurant insulted me. I do not expect to go to Asmara again. I would not recommend this restaurant unless you don't mind being insulted as part of her rude sense of humour. I literally lost my appetite!!! I learned my lesson.
Best restaurant. Best food and best service. I would give 10 out of 5 stars if I could!
Tasty food although small portions for price, great service and clean facility.
Great little gem, serving authentic Ethiopian cuisine.

Currently craving this restaurant’s amazing bread and offerings! I had the salmon and the chickpeas last time I was in and each dish was an explosion of spices that evoked comfort and finesse! Will be bringing some friends there so I can return soon!

Our group shared a platter of both the meat and non-meat combos.  Some dishes were VERY spicy.  Taking off one star as the server was not amenable to putting the two combos on separate platters, despite our saying we had a vegetarian in the group, plus she downright refused to give us forks when we asked as we didn’t really want to eat with our fingers.  What happened to ‘the customer is always right’?  Good food at a reasonable price, but I’m not sure I’d go again with that attitude.
Amazing food. Cannot understate how good it was. The food is served with a delicious bread that you use to pick up the meat. Be prepared for finger food
Simple, non-assuming establishment with great, helpful service, and wonderful tasty food. Loved it. Definitely going to be coming here regularly.
Super tasty food and friendly staff!
The food and help are great here. If you have never had African food this is the place to go
Great experience and food. It’s so cozy inside. Try the beer!
I love this place. The food is delicious and the owner is one of the nicest people I know (and I know a lot of people).

There is nothing to dislike about Eritrean food. You get to eat flavorful dishes with an edible utensil on an edible plate, while sipping honey wine or spiced tea loaded with cinnamon and clove. It's even better having this delightful culinary experience in a cozy spot with delightful staff while watching Eritrean music videos. The bloopers at the end are also fantastic. I can see why my friend Carolyn eats here every week. Thanks, Asmara!
Great and authentic food, with imported Eritrean beer even.
Been coming here for 19 years, it's a great lunch spot!  Freshly made food and juices!  If you are feeling bold, you have to try the kitfu!
The food was delicious. The authentic imported beer was a nice touch. Go to place for Ethiopian food in Cambridge not sure how Eritrean food differs but I will keep going back to figure it out.

Very flavorful food (shared the vegetarian combination platter with a friend, nice variety of veggies and spices) in a simple cozy atmosphere. Not too spicy, different, fun... you will have to use your fingers to gather the food on the injera (Ethiopian flat bread) although I imagine they would provide silverware if requested. Very friendly staff. Would definitely go again to try other specialties.
Enjoyed the vegetable platter
Excellent and inexpensive means. Very tasty and friendly.
Food was delicious and honey wine was also incredible. Go here and being a big crowd so you can try more things!!!

We had the vegetarian combination, the injera was very sour and almost inedible as the batter was clearly over fermented. The vegetables and lentils were tasteless. They have a decent ambience but overall a bad experience.
Really amazing, flavorful food! The service was pretty fast and the environment was great.
The food is incredible and the owner is super friendly.
Great staff, and interesting variation of spices in the dishes
Come for the sour bread, the lentil stew, the spices, the friendly staff, the unique experience.

Absolutely love this place, it's an old favorite of ours. Big flavors and really good options, both vegetarian and meat. Would recommend their vegetarian sampler and the meat special with chicken, beef, and lamb.

Not the best place in the area unfortunately. Lucy’s is much better in my opinion, although a further trek.  Asmara is beautifully decorated and the staff is very friendly. That is the extent of what I can compliment. The food is standard pricing for Ethiopian/Eritrean cuisine but somehow felt overpriced due to the quality. The meat was so dry and lacked flavor. The injera was thin and not spongey enough. The salad was also not great compared to other places (if I come back I would probably ask for no feta cheese.. it ruined the freshness of the salad).  All in all I would rather travel further to have better quality food.
I know food tastes great but disappointed recently as we planned to have lunch and shocked upon seeing it's closed until Aug, 5th 2019

Service was great. Friendly faces. First time trying Ethiopian food and it was such a great experience. Flavors were so delicious and full of life. Vegan friendly and even have a vegan dessert.  Loved the decor and the full Ethiopian meal experience of eating the injera with my hands.
DELICIOUS
What a delicious find! The vegetarian platter is huge and everything was absolutely amazing!  Recommend times 1000!

Excellent Eritrean food (very similar to Ethiopian) !! You can sit at a traditional woven table or a regular dining table. The service though not usually very fast, is friendly and personable - and clearly has a family owned feel to it. I always get the vegetarian combo platter with friends, which I personally prefer to the meat options. Vegan and vegetarian friendly. The food is delicious and you can ask for more injera - but budget stomach space to eat the flavor soaked injera plate your food is on!! Keep in mind that you won't be able to split multiple credit cards if you come here with friends though.
So good. Definitely recommend it.
Delicious healthy food, great for vegans!

(review I posted on Yelp in May 2018): Excellent experience. I am in Cambridge for 2 weeks for work and this is the first place i visited. i may only be here for 2 weeks but i will come back here before i leave!!! Excellent service, food, location and atmosphere.  I have never had Ethiopian cuisine before and the waitress asked if i had any questions about the cuisine...i didn't, until my food got served with no silverware! At which point she calmly and non-judgmental explained to me how to eat traditionally with fingers. I did as she instructed. It was so flavorful. So good. Cool experience.  Ambience was what I wanted, too. Quiet but audible traditional music playing, traditional tables, good artwork, nice tables, history in menus, etc. As good an experience as it gets. Highly recommend!!!
Soo delicious ,  homemade quality, great service, nice and welcoming staff.
Excellent vegan menu

This place is wonderful, I've really wanted to try Eritrean. Food was wonderful, so so good. They have vegan/vegetarian options if that's your thing. It is small, space wise so there could be a wait especially on like a weekend night. I don't think it's a quick meal kind of place, at least not at night. It's great for catching up or celebrating our something where you want to spend time with others. When I went it seemed like there was one waitress and a food runner and whoever was in the kitchen, which was really impressive, but that could be how it is regularly. Don't let that discourage you, it's worth it, and they were so nice too. I wish I lived in the area to go back sooner.
Food here is just great!! The waitress is super friendly. Recommend the wine!
If ten stars were available, would give it ten stars. Extremely good food, very friendly staff and authentic Ethiopian cuisine . Damn even the after eat candies are awesome

We ordered 3 meat combinations to share, totaling $45+ dollars and was given what looks like the portion for 1 person! The meats were dry and salty, and they replaced two sides of meat with vegetables without any explanations. I asked for some berbere (some spice like chili) and was told that it would cost similar to a main dish and even given attitude!!! Outrageous. Will never go back.
He km HD
Love love love live
Wonderful Ethiopian/Eritrean food with the unique experience of eating with your hands, excellent all around

The best Ethiopian/Eritrean cuisine you will experience in the Boston area.  Hands down.  'Nuff said.  Simply put, you are wasting your life if you do not go here and experience this intensely flavorful, freshly-crafted food firsthand.
On two separate occassions I tried going here for lunch and they were closed. Incredibly frustrating.
Very enjoyable trip to Asmara.  It was very busy but the meal was served quickly, the server was friendly and efficient.  Cozy and quaint atmosphere. Will definitely return.
Loved it. Very authentic feel. Health food. Unique dinning experience
Love Asmara. A little expensive and $1 per extra injera (which you may not even get if you order to go), but portions are large and better quality than other places in Boston.
Very good homemade mead, and a delicious buttery ground beef dish among others
When we walked in, they turned us away because the cook was an hour and a half late
Good Ethiopian food, but service was very slow

The food was really tasteful, with a combination of spices that dances in a colorful with your taste bud. I liked the atmosphere of then place, and I have enjoyed every bit of my get together here. Letti, one of he staff, was hands down the best the best, she was super welcoming, extremely helpful and accommodating.
(Translated by Google) Name name  (Original) Nom nom

I've been meaning to try Asmara for a while now and I'm glad I finally did. We got the meat combo, which was spectacular. Everything was full of flavor but still really well balanced. Definitely worth a try

Asmara is a great lunch spot! It has really delicious food and a variety of meat and vegetarian options. The staff is really friendly, helpful, and the service is pretty quick given the high quality!!!
not worth the pricing

Specially asked the waitress for 1 plate to share. At the end of the meal, the bill came after a long wait. I was charged for 2 meals, totaling over $50!! When I told her that she made a mistake, I was given an attitude and lied to about what I said. Terrible customer service and they over charge you. be careful.
Best Ethiopian food in Boston and always great service.  I love this place!
Too salty but it happens I forgive you
First time there, did was delicious.
Awesome experience!
There was a decent wait for a table as the time i went it appeared to be understaffed. The food, however, was great
Amazing experience. I ate the meat combo and loved it. I was very full at the end.

This is one of my favorite restaurants in the Boston area. I think both the meat and vegetarian options are very tasty. The staff are very friendly and the atmosphere is great. It's a smaller place so you may have to wait a bit but it's well worth it.
clean place, good staffs & fair food (not that spicy for a native like me).
Staple for Ethopian, I started going here in 1987! Food is outstanding...
Delicious food, and such a nice change from "the usual."  The spicy chicken lived up to its billing!  Super friendly staff with quick service which is appreciated at lunch time.
Got here at 9:50. They said the kitchen closes at 9:30 although their closing time is 10:30 pm.
Wonderful authentic eritrean/ethiopian food and over the top service
Good traditional food. They have both teff and 50/50 wheat/teff injera.
Great food for vegans. Call ahead to get injura gluten free

Delicious, flavorful Eritrean food with lovely ambience and friendly servers. The stuffed tomatoes with spiced rice were served on a bed of injera; they had a nice kick with a robust, almost meaty flavor even though they were vegetarian. The spinach and ricotta dish possessed a smooth texture that was also spicy and satisfying. It was served with injera as well. Both appetizers were wonderful introductions to the main meal that we chose, which were: -Sega Bebaynetu, a meat combination consisting of boneless chicken, spicy lamb, sautéed beef, and a mild vegetable stew, mild lentils and a house special salad; and -Ahimilti Bebaynetu, a vegetable combination of cabbage, yellow split peas, spinach, chick peas, lentils, and tomato salad. These two combination platters explode with delightful flavors and aromas; they're a wonderful sampling of many of the dishes they have, and we left the restaurant both satiated and wonderfully satisfied!

It's sad that I'm not reviewing the food considering I wasn't allowed access into the restaurant.  I travel with a service dog and have for the last 6 years.  Professionally, I speak about disability awareness. Last night, we were refused access to Asmara by a restaurant employee who claimed that service dogs are only for the blind. It's unfortunate that people can be so callous and she certainly didn't seem to want to be educated on the federal laws providing protections for people with all types of disabilities.  It's also unfortunate that the business owner and/or manager were no where to be found.  This young server should be required to take some ethics training along with learning about compassion for those with disabilities.  To date, the restaurant has not addressed the issue or apologized for her mistreatment of us.

Very unique eating experience. Good food and friendly service I recommend eating traditional-style for The Full Experience. Just wish they had turn the music down a little bit as it was a little too loud

Personally I did not like this place at all...it is way overpriced ...every item was overly sour in taste..chicken gravy was very bland...moreover all this was served with a wrong injera and upon asking we were served with a inconsiderate attitude....the same went on with our every request ....
The food is amazing and the staff is spectacular. I have always been treated warmly and welcoming, like coming home. 10 years of coming here and never disappointed.

We had an incredible meal! We ordered the veggie platter and meat platter. All of the food was spiced perfectly fine portions were good. Our server was very kind. And the place was packed!! We will definitely be back.

Important to note that its Eritrean NOT Ethiopian. But overall a very nice experience with the option to sit traditionally or at a normal table. The service is very good and they are very friendly. Authentic food; Authentic experience.

An excellent restaurant. Can get crowded on weekends with relatively long waits.  Our server every time I’ve gone has been the highlight of the experience. She is always so friendly and witty.  Great food as well at reasonably prices. Would recommend to anyone. Try on a weeknight to avoid more crowded times.

We love it here! Food is fantastic, friendly staff. Gets crowded and service can slow down--I honestly don't know how they do it with such minimal staff, but they always have a smile. Eat traditionally or at a regular table. The vegetarian platter is suitable for vegans. The only thing that bothers me here is the Eritrean music videos playing loudly in an endless loop.
Great authentic Ethiopian/Eritrean fare. Waitstaff were helpful in choosing entrees and service was quick. Would definitely go again!
Great food, gets crowded
Always a good experience.

1st experience with this type of cuisine. I love loved it. You get a choice of eating at a traditional or regular table. Recommend traditional for the whole experience thing. Having never tried this, the waitress recommended comination plates, explaining what each entailed. We went with that. She also told us about the bread and how to use the bread as an utensil. The amount of food was absolutely astounding! The flavors and aromas intoxicating. Its heaven for the herbivore, carnivore or omnivore in you. I had the tea also which was lovely with a nice cinnamon flavor. I dont know if the waitress was too sure I would like it. But loved it and would enjoy having it often. Sure wish there was food and service like this in my home state. The waitress explained how a meal would take a long time while the family catches up. So we were leisurely and she was right it is such a wonderful experience!!
The best food in Boston.

Fantastic food, fantastic breakfast both for vegetarians and non-vegetarians. Staff is wonderful - really patient, and offering to go above and beyond unprompted. The dishes seem to be a bit on the pricey side, but it is nearly impossible for a single person to finish a portion in one sitting - make sure to order extra injera (the delicious crepe-like bread) and either enjoy awesome leftovers at home for another meal or two, or eat family-style with your dining companion(s).
Great food and great staff. I enjoy every plate I eat here.

Really good Eritrean food, its very authentic and the staff is very friendly and helpful. The few times I have been it has been a great experience. The coffee is pretty cool too they serve it in a little wooden flask, very authentic.
This place has one of the best house salads I have ever had. Combine it with Injera and your are all set. Small and very peaceful with nice asmara music playing in the background.
The food and service is great! My second time having Ethiopian food and I really love the food :) Worth trying!

My first experience with an Eritrean/Ethiopian cuisine.  I was very reluctant as I am a vegetarian.  We had Ahimliti Bebaynatu-vegetarian combination and traditional Ethiopian coffee.  The vegetarian dish with Injeria Bread was very delicious and it was an experience.  The coffee was excellent(black coffee, remember they do not have sugar free packets).  Great service too
So good! I had been missing Ethiopian food, and this hit the spot. The format of the service is fun too, and the atmosphere is very relaxed.

Asmara... I have always wanted to try Ethiopian cuisine and I am glad I ended up at this place.  This place is located on the busy Mass Ave close to Central square. Parking can be a problem in rush hour and weekends. It's easy to find as it is on the main road.  The ambience gives the native etireanean and Ethiopian feel. They have both normal tables and the traditional knit tables( dining on them highly recommended).  The food was great. We ordered vegetarian combo with greens, lentils, spicy sauce, cabbage , injera and excellent tomato jalapeno salad.  The traditional music plays in a low volume.  +5 to the cleanest restrooms.

I go to Asmara very often. The food is delicious, and the service is fantastic. The weitress who works on evenings is really welcoming and nice. The music is quite low, making it easy to chat with your party.
Very good food, love it. I recommend to go if you like to try different kind of foods
Excellent food. It is an experience that everyone should have. The food is amazingly tasty. Would highly recommend it. Good spicy food in Boston.
A great place to fulfill your needs for Eritrean cuisine. I'm especially partial to the lamb. The food is slightly on the spicier side but, that's the way I like it.
Great food! Great staff, loved the place
Love this place to food is good the service is friendly The Taste is consistent and delicious. My daughter and I love to come here
Probably the best Erithian restaurant in Cambridge. Excellent service
Best Ethiopian / Eritrean restaurant in the Boston area. Slow service. Staff give you startled looks when you ask for utensils, which lends some appreciated authenticity.
Cozy atmosphere, great food &service
Delicious Ethiopian food! Happy to find a staple like this in Cambridge!

Ethiopian food is just, well, it never disappoints. But it's even better at Asmara. From the cozy ambience, which is great whether it's date night or food and drinks with friends, to the delicious food itself and generous portions, this place is the truth.
Very enjoyable.  Waitress is wonderful.
Great all around experience. You won't regret going. Fun for a group.
Food is always good and staff is very friendly.
Always closed. Went there twice just for the love of Ethiopian food...
First time being there. The food was so good and the people were helpful and lovely. Can't wait to go back.
Simply the best !
Love this place. Great food and friendly folks.
Good food, good atmosphere, and kind staff. Best Ethiopian in Boston!
classic ethopian...

Seriously the best Ethiopian (or the capital of Ethiopia specifically, I forget the name) food I have ever had. The waitress is always wonderful and service is great. I'd highly recommend trying this place out, especially if you've never had Ethiopian food before.
Food is yumm!!
Great food and special experience no silverware:)
Terrible food.  Went here with some friends last winter, what we were served was a long wait, overly sour injera, and supremely bland food.
The food is really tasty. Try Kitfo, it is really good! The prices are very decent given the location of the restaurant. And the place itself is very small and cozy.
Great food. Option to eat communally, Eritrean style. Quiet environment. Great service.
Excellent Ehtiopian food -- especially if you like it spicy.  Strongly recommend either the combo platter that includes meat or the veggie combo platter.
Sabba is the best hoste around.

I love this place. I've been coming here for years. If you call ahead the morning you're going, they will make their normally 95% gluten free teff pancakes 100% gluten free. Get a sampler platter your first time (or every time like I do). You can get meat, vegetarian or both (I'd suggest both).  The primary uniqueness is the sour flavor of the food combined with spiciness (not too much spice - I'm a heat wimp, so if I can eat it, you'll likely be ok too).  The owner is a wonderful woman too - always friendly - and I love the straw tables.
so good. small but comfortable. great staff. worth the wait if and when there is one.

We ordered take out (since the restaurant itself was small and we hadn't called ahead to book a table for 6). The food was delicious and im guessing freshly made (since we had to wait FOREVER to get it). I only docked one point off since service was poor, only one waitress and one server to handle some 30 odd dinners.

I arrived at the restaurant at 2 PM on 05/09/17 to have lunch. I went to the bathroom, and the waitress stopped me from going to the bathroom, said that the restaurant was closed and that the bathroom was for customers only. There were other people having lunch there, the sign on the door was open, and the restaurant works normally at that time. I explained to the waitress that I was a client, that I would go to the bathroom and come back to make the request, and that my girlfriend would be at the table. The waitress refused to answer me, said that I could not use the bathroom, that the restaurant was closed and expelled me from the restaurant. I've never been so humiliated and mistreated. Terrible experience at this restaurant. I feel that I suffered prejudice. Would not recommend to anyone at this restaurant.
A different way to eat, excellent food.
Good service
Great food but in small portion for me.
Twice came by, and it was closed during its posted open hours. Don't know if it's closed for Good.
Loved the salad in the middle! Food was nicely spicy :) (I had to wash everything I was wearing because it smelled so strongly :P)
Decent food.  Injera a little dry.  Good options for vegetarians.
Wonderful Eritrean food. They have a lovely vegetarian combo that can be enough for two on its own.

Asmara is a really good Ethiopian-style restaurant. For those of you who haven't eaten Ethiopian food before, it's really cool: it comes on a massive plate covered in spongy Injera bread (made from teff flour; gluten free) that you eat by tearing off bits of bread and using it to scope up the toppings. Very fun finger food.
good food!

Family run ethiopian restaurant. There are no reservations from my recollection, best bet is to go when dinner service starts or nearing when they're about to close to avoid the queue. Can't go wrong with their meat platter which allows you to sample a bit of everything. the service is very friendly and is reasonably priced. If possible, try to get one of their wicker-basket tables to get a more authentic experience!
The food is classic Ethiopian and it is spectacular. Nothing compares to a dish of sega bebanyatu shared between two people and paired with mes honey wine.

I ordered meat combo with a vegetarian dish and salad and taste was terrible. I ordered 1 meal but they gave me 2 of the same food and had to pay for both of them. What can you do when it's your word against the waitress? Don't recommend it for sure.
Every time I visit Cambridge I eat here.  Have loved this place for decades
Superb!
Great food, slow service.
The food is delicious!
A bit overpriced 24$ for 1 person but food is great and authentic
Waiter pushes you to buy items you don't want. Quantity is very less
Decent Ethiopian place
It was good
A small place with nice spicy food. The service can be quite slow though. There is only 1 server who takes orders.
Very unpretentious but great food. Combo meals more mild than individual plates. Both western seating and traditional seating.
Nice staff. Pretty spicy food, you have been warned.
As a white European, I can't comment on how well this food represents Eritrea. I can say, however, that it's delicious.
Our favorite Ethiopian place
Great food And service..desserts were also amazing

Great, knowledgeable staff. For those unaware, the food is shareable, and comes altogether on a grain from which each customer can eat. My food (a chicken item) was well-spiced, and not pricey at all.
This food was really bad I prefer blue Nile in Jamaica plain!!!!!!
Delicious food and friendly service. A great choice for the health conscious who also enjoy a very tasty meal.

The traditional Ethiopian food is very good. Our injiri bread stayed soft through the entire meal, unlike at some other places I've been to. The spiced Asmara tea and homemade honey wine are both excellent. The main drawback to the place is its ambiance. While the woven basket tables give the restaurant a simultaneously ethnic and homey feel, the African tribal music videos add little to the place. There is no hostess station to welcome you when enter, and you may need to wait quite a while for a table without knowing how long to expect.
Poor selection of beers.  Food ok.
Unique dining experience with even better food.
Excellent restaurant. The food is top-notch, so good, and healthy too. The service is wonderful. I come here regularly.
Eritean,Ethiopian food..who knew how the combating of Italian and African food would taste so good...hard to decide what we liked best..family style eating
My favorite restaurant in the area. Food is amazing, and the owners are lovely people!
Delicious! Friendly service, wonderful flavors, right in Central square.

Our new favorite Ethiopian (Eritrean) restaurant! They have fantastic gluten free injera and all their dishes are great. They have shuro (my favorite) along with our other favorites. Atmosphere is amazing and it is a lot of fun to sit at the authentic tables. This is a much more traditional experience than some other places we've tried in the Boston area and we loved it.  We'll be coming back often.

I crave the spicy Shuro (chickpea) dish from Asmara frequently. It's so flavorful , comforting and filling. All of the vegetarian dishes are great but the Hamil (collard greens) and Tomato Salad are particularly nice with the shuro and injera. On a side note, if you let them know in advance they can make gluten free injera (the bread).

This authentic restaurant offered amazing Ethiopian Eritrean food. As is usual with Ethiopian food, finding vegan options was not a problem. The staff was very friendly and accommodating.  What I loved about this place were the traditional tables/baskets on which the shared platter is served. I also enjoyed that they described some of the history of Eritrea on the menu, as well as some of its traditions.  The food was a little more pricey than most places in Cambridge, but it was excellent quality and they served large portions.
Service is OK but the food is great especially for vegetarians.

Wonderful service and very flavorful food. The combination plates are lovely; you get a nice variety of flavors and it's a great way to feed a group.  If you've never tried Eritrean or Ethiopian food, the basic concept and flavor profile is similar to a lot of Indian and Middle Eastern dishes: lentils and vegetables and chunks of meat stewed in various sauces.

I go out of my way to eat Ethiopian food and this place is great. The food is great, the service is warm and speedy, and they have a great Ethiopian beer. Also a nice menu with a wide range of choices. They also serve the whole grain injera and that's a huge plus in my book if you want good Ethiopian food.

Really nice Ethiopian restaurant - very authentic feel to it, and really tasty food.

I love injera, the smushy bread that comes with Ethiopian cuisine. I mean I love injera so much that I will regularly hold it softly against my cheek and sigh wistfully before consuming it. The bread at Asmara is fluffy, soft, and just a bit sour from the fermented teff used to make it. It's excellent, I mean really really excellent. Sadly, the food seems to err on the side of bland. My collard greens were well cooked but tasted mainly one-note and the yellow lentils had barely any flavor beyond "This is a lentil." My companion and I wanted to share their vegetarian sampler and were instructed by the waitress that it "served one." Served one person for $16? Well alright. Once ordered, it was obvious that one would have been sufficient when paired with an appetizer, and we felt we had been swindled a bit into over ordering.  Why three stars? The food here is authentic and good, but the prices are just a bit crazy. I've been to other Ethiopian restaurants (Addis comes to mind) where the portions were even more plentiful, and more importantly-- flavorful and prices cheaper, and the food quality was just as good if not better. Is their priciness due to location? I couldn't say. But for ho-hum service and not  particularly impressive food, I have to say I'd rather go elsewhere for Ethiopian, even if their injera is fabulous. I just wish the rest of their food was as tasty.
It's an experience eating here. For good.
